  "text": "## TLS Certificate Validation Logic in Envoy v1.31.2\n\n### Overview\nIdentified comprehensive certificate validation implementation across multiple files in the Envoy TLS stack, handling both server and client certificate validation scenarios.\n\n### Key Certificate Validator Implementations\n\n#### 1. Default Certificate Validator\n**Location**: `source/common/tls/cert_validator/default_validator.cc|.h`\n\nThis is the primary certificate validation implementation implementing the CertValidator interface. Key functions:\n- `initializeSslContexts()`: Sets up verification modes (SSL_VERIFY_PEER, SSL_VERIFY_NONE, SSL_VERIFY_FAIL_IF_NO_PEER_CERT). Returns verify_mode flag that controls certificate verification behavior.\n- `doVerifyCertChain()`: Performs certificate chain validation using X509_verify_cert() at line 315. Validates against CA certificates, CRL, certificate hashes, SPKI, and Subject Alt Names.\n- `addClientValidationContext()`: Called on server side to configure client certificate validation (line 481-543). Sets up CA list and verification depth using SSL_CTX_set_verify() (line 528).\n- `verifyCertificate()`: Custom verification logic for certificate attributes (SAN, hash, SPKI).\n\n**Certificate Validation References**:\n- Line 315: `X509_verify_cert(ctx.get())` - Performs X.509 certificate chain verification\n- Line 528: `SSL_CTX_set_verify()` - Client certificate validation on server side\n- Line 59-61: `verify_mode` variables controlling SSL verification behavior\n\n#### 2. SPIFFE Certificate Validator\n**Location**: `source/extensions/transport_sockets/tls/cert_validator/spiffe/spiffe_validator.cc|.h`\n\nSpecialized validator for SPIFFE certificate validation. Key functions:\n- `initializeSslContexts()`: Returns SSL_VERIFY_PEER | SSL_VERIFY_FAIL_IF_NO_PEER_CERT (line 146).\n- `doVerifyCertChain()`: Orchestrates SPIFFE-specific validation.\n- `verifyCertChainUsingTrustBundleStore()`: Performs actual verification using X509_verify_cert() (line 177). Uses per-trust-domain X509_STORE for validation.\n- `addClientValidationContext()`: Configures client certificate validation.\n\n**Certificate Validation References**:\n- Line 177: `X509_verify_cert(new_store_ctx.get())` - Core X.509 verification\n- Line 168-169: X509_STORE_CTX setup and initialization\n- Line 102: X509_STORE_set_flags with CRL checking flags\n\n#### 3. Context Implementation (Base TLS Context Setup)\n**Location**: `source/common/tls/context_impl.cc|.h`\n\nHandles SSL context initialization and custom verification callback setup:\n- Line 164-185: Initializes verify_mode from cert_validator_->initializeSslContexts(). Sets up SSL_CTX_set_custom_verify() callback for asynchronous verification.\n- Line 181: `SSL_CTX_set_custom_verify(ctx, verify_mode, customVerifyCallback)` - Sets the custom verification callback.\n- `customVerifyCallback()`: Static callback invoked by BoringSSL during TLS handshake to perform certificate validation.\n- `customVerifyCertChain()`: Delegates to cert_validator_->doVerifyCertChain() for actual validation logic.\n\n**Certificate Validation References**:\n- Line 181: SSL_CTX_set_custom_verify - Sets verification callback\n- Line 171: SSL_VERIFY_NONE check\n- Line 516: SSL_get_peer_full_cert_chain() - Retrieves peer certificate chain\n- Line 531-534: Calls cert_validator_->doVerifyCertChain()\n\n#### 4. Server Context Implementation\n**Location**: `source/common/tls/server_context_impl.cc|.h`\n\nServer-side TLS context setup including client certificate validation:\n- Line 147-148: Calls `cert_validator_->addClientValidationContext()` to configure client certificate validation when `requireClientCertificate()` is set.\n- Handles multi-certificate configurations for SNI matching.\n\n**Client Certificate Validation**:\n- Requires client certificates when `config.requireClientCertificate()` is true\n- Server validates incoming client certificates using configured validation context\n\n#### 5. Client Context Implementation\n**Location**: `source/common/tls/client_context_impl.cc|.h`\n\nClient-side TLS context setup including server certificate validation:\n- Line 114: `SSL_set_verify(ssl_con.get(), SSL_VERIFY_PEER | SSL_VERIFY_FAIL_IF_NO_PEER_CERT, nullptr)` - Enables server certificate verification when SAN overrides are provided.\n- Handles SNI (Server Name Indication) setup.\n\n**Server Certificate Validation**:\n- Verifies server certificates when verifySubjectAltNameListOverride is configured\n- Custom verification logic via customVerifyCallback chain\n\n### Certificate Validation Flow\n\n**Server-side (validating client certificates)**:\n1. ServerContextImpl initializes context via ContextImpl\n2. ContextImpl calls cert_validator_->addClientValidationContext()\n3. DefaultCertValidator/SPIFFEValidator sets SSL_CTX_set_client_CA_list() and optionally SSL_CTX_set_verify()\n4. During TLS handshake, client certificate is presented\n5. customVerifyCallback is invoked → customVerifyCertChain → doVerifyCertChain\n6. DefaultCertValidator performs X509_verify_cert() against configured CA certificates\n\n**Client-side (validating server certificates)**:\n1. ClientContextImpl initializes context via ContextImpl\n2. ContextImpl calls cert_validator_->initializeSslContexts() to get verify_mode\n3. ContextImpl sets up SSL_CTX_set_custom_verify() with customVerifyCallback\n4. During TLS handshake, server certificate is presented\n5. customVerifyCallback is invoked → customVerifyCertChain → doVerifyCertChain\n6. DefaultCertValidator performs X509_verify_cert() against configured CA certificates\n\n### Certificate Validation Features\n\n**Supported Verification Modes**:\n- SSL_VERIFY_NONE: No verification required\n- SSL_VERIFY_PEER: Verify peer certificate if provided\n- SSL_VERIFY_FAIL_IF_NO_PEER_CERT: Fail if peer doesn't provide certificate\n\n**Custom Validation Logic**:\n- Subject Alt Name (SAN) verification\n- Certificate hash pinning (SHA256)\n- Subject Public Key Info (SPKI) verification\n- CRL (Certificate Revocation List) checking\n- Certificate expiration override\n- Trust chain depth verification\n\n### Key Files Summary\n\n| File | Purpose | Validation Type |\n|------|---------|------------------|\n| default_validator.cc/h | Default certificate validator | Both server & client |\n| spiffe_validator.cc/h | SPIFFE certificate validator | Both server & client |\n| context_impl.cc/h | Base TLS context & verification callback | Both server & client |\n| server_context_impl.cc/h | Server-side context setup | Client cert validation |\n| client_context_impl.cc/h | Client-side context setup | Server cert validation |\n| cert_validator.h | Abstract validator interface | Definition |\n| utility.cc/h | Cert validation utilities (expiration override) | Supporting |\n\n### Critical Verification Functions\n\n1. **X509_verify_cert()** - Core OpenSSL certificate chain verification (used in default_validator.cc:315, spiffe_validator.cc:177)\n2. **SSL_CTX_set_verify()** - Sets verification mode and callback (default_validator.cc:528)\n3. **SSL_CTX_set_custom_verify()** - Sets custom verification callback (context_impl.cc:181)\n4. **SSL_CTX_set_verify_depth()** - Sets maximum verification depth (default_validator.cc:540)\n5. **X509_STORE_add_cert()** - Adds certificate to trust store (default_validator.cc:92, spiffe_validator.cc:81)\n6. **X509_STORE_set_flags()** - Sets CRL checking flags (default_validator.cc:88, 137, 143)\n"
